summary: This document is an email chain from May 2020 between federal prosecutors and law enforcement agents discussing the status of FBI 302 interview reports and handwritten notes related to the Epstein investigation. The correspondence involves tracking down missing documents and clarifying which interviews have associated notes versus formal reports.
keyFacts: The email chain reveals coordination between Assistant U.S. Attorneys and law enforcement agents regarding Epstein case interview documentation.
The correspondence mentions more than 120 interviews were conducted in the case, indicating the investigation's extensive scope.
The emails discuss specific missing FBI 302 reports and handwritten interview notes that needed to be tracked down.
The document shows ongoing document management and verification efforts in May 2020, well after Epstein's death.
Multiple names appear to be redacted or referenced only by initials in the text, preventing identification of specific individuals.
